<subSubSection pageId="null" pageNumber="367" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="null" pageNumber="367">
Unterscheidet sich von 
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Serrafalcus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="null" pageNumber="367" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="secalinus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="367">B. secalinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Nr. 12) durch folgende Merkmale: 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="367">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Rispenäste" pageId="null" pageNumber="367">Rispenaeste</normalizedToken>
behaart;
</emphasis>
<normalizedToken originalValue="Ährchen" pageId="null" pageNumber="367">Aehrchen</normalizedToken>
meist 
<normalizedToken originalValue="größer" pageId="null" pageNumber="367">groesser</normalizedToken>
, 2-3 cm lang, 10-15 
<normalizedToken originalValue="blütig" pageId="null" pageNumber="367">bluetig</normalizedToken>
. 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="367">
Deckspelzen 10-12 mm lang, etwa um 1,5 mm 
<normalizedToken originalValue="länger" pageId="null" pageNumber="367">laenger</normalizedToken>
als die Vorspelzen
</emphasis>
. - 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Blüte" pageId="null" pageNumber="367">Bluete</normalizedToken>
: Sommer und Herbst.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="null" pageNumber="367">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="367">Zytologische Angaben. 2n = 28:</emphasis>
Material aus Frankreich (Cugnac und Simonet 1941).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="null" pageNumber="367">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="367">Standort</emphasis>
. Kollin und montan. Wie 
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Serrafalcus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="null" pageNumber="367" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="secalinus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="367">B. secalinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Nr. 12). Nach Braun-Blanquet (1949) kommt in 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Graubünden" pageId="null" pageNumber="367">Graubuenden</normalizedToken>
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Serrafalcus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="null" pageNumber="367" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="secalinus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="367">B. secalinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
auf kalkhaltigen, 
<normalizedToken originalValue="durchlässigen" pageId="null" pageNumber="367">durchlaessigen</normalizedToken>
Schottern in 
<normalizedToken originalValue="heißen" pageId="null" pageNumber="367">heissen</normalizedToken>
, lufttrockenen Lagen im 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="367">Adonieto-Delphinietum consolidae</emphasis>
Br.-Bl. 1949 vor.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="null" pageNumber="367">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="367">Verbreitung. Eurasiatische Pflanze:</emphasis>
Wie 
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Serrafalcus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="null" pageNumber="367" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="secalinus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="367">B. secalinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Nr. 12).
</paragraph>
